    "body": "**Description of the problem**\r\n\r\nHere is the test script to generate a discrete CPT and plot it:\r\n```\r\ngmt begin colorbar\r\n\tgmt makecpt -Ccategorical -W -T0/10/1\r\n\tgmt colorbar -C -B -Dx0c/0c+w10c+h\r\ngmt end show\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn GMT 6.3, the colorbar looks bad using Apple Preview (see below):\r\n<img width=\"1077\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3974108/165129614-193dd2a0-c6a7-4e9d-9f2e-f8ee09d11548.png\">\r\n\r\nPR https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/gmt/pull/6360 fixes the problem by plotting rectangles for discrete colorbars. After the fix, the PDF version of the new image looks good, but the PNG version is not perfect if you zoom in to check the details. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"407\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3974108/165130591-f846e470-61b8-4f42-a767-87649c2d6c31.png\">\r\n\r\nPerhaps it's because the polygons are overlapping?",
